page.title: 07TURLIN MOOR
page.content: {Turlin Moor This area is mainly{residential. }It is a quiet area with few cars. The houses are mostly terraced or semi- detached and there are also several blocks of flats. The buildings are quite new with small neat gardens and the flats have grassy areas around them. There are some small{shops}and {schools;}Turlin Moor First and Turlin Moor Middle School. A{railway line}cuts through the area from{Hamworthy Junction}to{Rockley {Viaduct}and there is a regular bus service. It is very easy to get lost in Turlin Moor because there are lots of small paths and some of the roads are labelled the same. The area is bordered by{mudflats}and {the River Lea.
